sonusTrunkGroupResourcesMIB.description: The MIB Module for Trunk Group Resources Management.

sonusTgMaxRpcLpcs.name: sonusTgMaxRpcLpcs
sonusTgMaxRpcLpcs.description: Maximum number of RPC-LPC pairs for this gateway.

sonusTgMaxCics.name: sonusTgMaxCics
sonusTgMaxCics.description: Maximum number of CICs for this gateway.

sonusTgMaxTrunkGroups.name: sonusTgMaxTrunkGroups
sonusTgMaxTrunkGroups.description: Maximum number of trunk groups for this gateway.

sonusTgMaxServiceGroups.name: sonusTgMaxServiceGroups
sonusTgMaxServiceGroups.description: Maximum number of Service Groups for this gateway.

sonusTgMaxSgInstances.name: sonusTgMaxSgInstances
sonusTgMaxSgInstances.description: Maximum number of Service Group Instances for this gateway.

sonusTgNextIndex.name: sonusTgNextIndex
sonusTgNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating a new sonusTgEntry

sonusTgTable.name: sonusTgTable
sonusTgTable.description: A list of trunk group entries.

sonusTgEntry.name: sonusTgEntry
sonusTgEntry.description: Each sonusTgEntry containing configuration objects. Rules & Behaviors: A sonusTgEntry cannot be deleted when it is enabled. When disabling the trunk group entry, it must not have any associated SGs. All SGs must be removed before disabling the trunk group. A sonusTgEntry cannot be modified when it is enabled.

sonusTgIndex.name: sonusTgIndex
sonusTgIndex.description: A unique value for each trunk group that is between 1 and maximum allowed

sonusTgName.name: sonusTgName
sonusTgName.description: The name of the trunk group.

sonusTgProfName.name: sonusTgProfName
sonusTgProfName.description: The name of the profile applied to this trunk group entry.

sonusTgSgSelect.name: sonusTgSgSelect
sonusTgSgSelect.description: Selection for hunting within a PSTN trunk group that has more than 1 associated service group(SG). It is either based on cost associated with each SG, how the SG is ordered during configuration (for circular also). If either circular option is chosen, then SG hunt algorithm is ignored.

sonusTgLnpTranslate.name: sonusTgLnpTranslate
sonusTgLnpTranslate.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that may require LNP translation for the called number.

sonusTg800Translate.name: sonusTg800Translate
sonusTg800Translate.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that may require 800 number translation for the called number.

sonusTgCallingNumVerify.name: sonusTgCallingNumVerify
sonusTgCallingNumVerify.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that requires verification for the calling number.

sonusTgInboundReserved.name: sonusTgInboundReserved
sonusTgInboundReserved.description: This is only meaninful for PSTN Trunk Groups. This the percent of channels reserved for handling inbound calls. Default is 0% and valid for both direction type trunks. The amount reserved is round off to next number. For example, 50% of 23 hannels is 12.5 or 13 channels. Percentage selection allowed in 5% increments.

sonusTgIsupOnly.name: sonusTgIsupOnly
sonusTgIsupOnly.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that is either an ISUP only or mixed of ISUP and other PSTN types

sonusTgCarrier.name: sonusTgCarrier
sonusTgCarrier.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups and is specific to Isup only. This is the name of the Isup that this trunk group is bound to.

sonusTgIsupNode.name: sonusTgIsupNode
sonusTgIsupNode.description: This is meaningful for PSTN trunk groups and is specific to Isup only. This is the name of the Isup that this trunk group is bound to.

sonusTgAdminState.name: sonusTgAdminState
sonusTgAdminState.description: Administrative state to disable or enable a trunk group. All trunk groups are created with its state disabled. If trunk group is disabled, the trunk group must be enabled to allow calls to proceed.

sonusTgMode.name: sonusTgMode
sonusTgMode.description: The operation mode for this trunk.

sonusTgAction.name: sonusTgAction
sonusTgAction.description: The action for the operation mode for this trunk.

sonusTgTimeout.name: sonusTgTimeout
sonusTgTimeout.description: Timeout value in minutes for the dry up action.

sonusTgCirResvState.name: sonusTgCirResvState
sonusTgCirResvState.description: Administrative state to disable or enable the circuit reservation feature on a trunk group. All trunk groups are created with this feature disabled. If this feature is enabled, the sonusTgInboundReserved feature is overriden automatically.

sonusTgPriorityCallReserve.name: sonusTgPriorityCallReserve
sonusTgPriorityCallReserve.description: The minimum number of priority call allowed set for this trunk group when sonusTgCirResvState is set to enabled.

sonusTgIncomingCallReserve.name: sonusTgIncomingCallReserve
sonusTgIncomingCallReserve.description: The minimum number of incoming call allowed set for this trunk group when sonusTgCirResvState is set to enabled.

sonusTgOutgoingCallReserve.name: sonusTgOutgoingCallReserve
sonusTgOutgoingCallReserve.description: The minimum percent of outgoing call allowed set for this trunk group when sonusTgCirResvState is set to enabled.

sonusTgStatusTable.name: sonusTgStatusTable
sonusTgStatusTable.description: This table contains status information of a PSTN trunk group. There may not be any SG registered to a trunk group in which case all statistics will be zero.

sonusTgStatusEntry.name: sonusTgStatusEntry
sonusTgStatusEntry.description: Each entry describes the current status of a PSTN trunk group.

sonusTgStatusIndex.name: sonusTgStatusIndex
sonusTgStatusIndex.description: A unique value for each trunk group between 1 and maximum allowed.

sonusTgOperState.name: sonusTgOperState
sonusTgOperState.description: Current operational state of the trunk group.

sonusTgPstnTotalAvailable.name: sonusTgPstnTotalAvailable
sonusTgPstnTotalAvailable.description: The sum of all available or unblocked PSTN channels for this trunk group.

sonusTgPstnTotalInboundRsv.name: sonusTgPstnTotalInboundRsv
sonusTgPstnTotalInboundRsv.description: This is meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that are configured for inbound or both directions only. This is the reserved count as specified by the percentage configred for this trunk group.

sonusTgPstnInboundUsage.name: sonusTgPstnInboundUsage
sonusTgPstnInboundUsage.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that are configured for inbound or both directions. This reflects the current inbound or incoming usage count of this trunk group.

sonusTgPstnOutboundUsage.name: sonusTgPstnOutboundUsage
sonusTgPstnOutboundUsage.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that are configured for outbound or both directions. This reflects the current outbound, outgoing or non-priority usage count of this trunk group.

sonusTgPstnTotalConfigured.name: sonusTgPstnTotalConfigured
sonusTgPstnTotalConfigured.description: The sum of all configured and registered PSTN channels for this trunk group.

sonusTgAccCurrentACL.name: sonusTgAccCurrentACL
sonusTgAccCurrentACL.description: Current congestion level for the Trunk Group

sonusTgPriorityCallUsage.name: sonusTgPriorityCallUsage
sonusTgPriorityCallUsage.description: This is only meaningful for ISUP trunk groups that are configured and when sonusTgCirResvState is enabled. This reflects the current priority usage count of this trunk group.

sonusTgSgTable.name: sonusTgSgTable
sonusTgSgTable.description: This is a virtual table containing a list of service groups that belong to the same trunk group. This is a doubly indexed table so that further details about each service group may be queried by name.

sonusTgSgEntry.name: sonusTgSgEntry
sonusTgSgEntry.description: Each entry lists the name and order of each service group.

sonusTgSgTgIndex.name: sonusTgSgTgIndex
sonusTgSgTgIndex.description: The Trunk Group index that has the following set of Service Groups.

sonusTgSgIndex.name: sonusTgSgIndex
sonusTgSgIndex.description: A unique value for each service group in this trunk group

sonusTgSgName.name: sonusTgSgName
sonusTgSgName.description: The name of the service group.

sonusTgSgType.name: sonusTgSgType
sonusTgSgType.description: The type of the service group.

sonusTgProfileNextIndex.name: sonusTgProfileNextIndex
sonusTgProfileNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating a new sonusTgProfileEntry

sonusTgProfileTable.name: sonusTgProfileTable
sonusTgProfileTable.description: A list of trunk group entries.

sonusTgProfileEntry.name: sonusTgProfileEntry
sonusTgProfileEntry.description: Each sonusTgProfileEntry containing configuration objects. Rules & Behaviors: A sonusTgProfileEntry cannot be deleted when it is enabled. When disabling the trunk group entry, it must not have any associated SGs. All SGs must be removed before disabling the trunk group. A sonusTgProfileEntry cannot be modified when it is enabled.

sonusTgProfileIndex.name: sonusTgProfileIndex
sonusTgProfileIndex.description: A unique value for each trunk group profile that is between 1 and maximum allowed

sonusTgProfileName.name: sonusTgProfileName
sonusTgProfileName.description: The name of this trunk group Profile.

sonusTgProfileSgSelect.name: sonusTgProfileSgSelect
sonusTgProfileSgSelect.description: Selection for hunting within a PSTN trunk group that has more than 1 associated service group(SG). It is based on cost associated with each SG, how the SG is ordered during configuration (for circular also). If either circular option is chosen, then SG hunt algorithm is ignored.

sonusTgProfileAdminState.name: sonusTgProfileAdminState
sonusTgProfileAdminState.description: Administrator state to use a trunk group Profile. All trunk group profiles are created with its state disabled. When disabled, the profile must be enabled to allowed to be used.

sonusTgProfileInboundReserved.name: sonusTgProfileInboundReserved
sonusTgProfileInboundReserved.description: This is only meaninful for PSTN Trunk Groups. This the percent of channels reserved for handling inbound calls. Default is 0% and valid for both direction type trunks. The amount reserved is round off to next number. For example, 50% of 23 hannels is 12.5 or 13 channels. Percentage selection allowed in 5% increments.

sonusTgProfileLnpTranslate.name: sonusTgProfileLnpTranslate
sonusTgProfileLnpTranslate.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that may require LNP translation for the called number.

sonusTgProfile800Translate.name: sonusTgProfile800Translate
sonusTgProfile800Translate.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that may require 800 number translation for the called number.

sonusTgProfileCallingNumVerify.name: sonusTgProfileCallingNumVerify
sonusTgProfileCallingNumVerify.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that requires verification for the calling number.

sonusTgProfileIsupOnly.name: sonusTgProfileIsupOnly
sonusTgProfileIsupOnly.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups that is either an ISUP only or mixed of ISUP and other PSTN types

sonusTgProfileCarrier.name: sonusTgProfileCarrier
sonusTgProfileCarrier.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups and is specific to Isup only. This is the name of the Isup that this trunk group is bound to.

sonusTgProfileIsupNode.name: sonusTgProfileIsupNode
sonusTgProfileIsupNode.description: This is only meaningful for PSTN trunk groups and is specific to Isup only. This is the name of the Isup that this trunk group is bound to.

sonusTgProfSgSelectState.name: sonusTgProfSgSelectState
sonusTgProfSgSelectState.description: Indicates whether sonusTgProfileSgSelect object is present in this profile

sonusTgProfInboundReservedState.name: sonusTgProfInboundReservedState
sonusTgProfInboundReservedState.description: Indicates whether sonusTgProfileInboundReserved object is present in this profile

sonusTgProfLnpTranslateState.name: sonusTgProfLnpTranslateState
sonusTgProfLnpTranslateState.description: Indicates whether sonusTgProfileLnpTranslate object is present in this profile

sonusTgProf800TranslateState.name: sonusTgProf800TranslateState
sonusTgProf800TranslateState.description: Indicates whether sonusTgProfile800Translate object is present in this profile

sonusTgProfCallingNumVerifyState.name: sonusTgProfCallingNumVerifyState
sonusTgProfCallingNumVerifyState.description: Indicates whether sonusTgProfileCallingNumVerify object is present in this profile

sonusTgProfIsupOnlyState.name: sonusTgProfIsupOnlyState
sonusTgProfIsupOnlyState.description: Indicates whether sonusTgProfileIsupOnly object is present in this profile

sonusTgProfCarrierState.name: sonusTgProfCarrierState
sonusTgProfCarrierState.description: Indicates whether sonusTgProfileCarrier object is present in this profile

sonusTgProfIsupNodeState.name: sonusTgProfIsupNodeState
sonusTgProfIsupNodeState.description: Indicates whether sonusTgProfileIsupNode object is present in this profile

sonusTgMaxGateways.name: sonusTgMaxGateways
sonusTgMaxGateways.description: Maximum allowable destination or remote gateways in the configuration.

sonusGatewayNextIndex.name: sonusGatewayNextIndex
sonusGatewayNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating a new sonusGatewayEntry

sonusGatewayTable.name: sonusGatewayTable
sonusGatewayTable.description: This is a table containing a list of IP telephony gateways in the network.

sonusGatewayEntry.name: sonusGatewayEntry
sonusGatewayEntry.description: Each entry lists the name and order of each gateway.

sonusGatewayIndex.name: sonusGatewayIndex
sonusGatewayIndex.description: A unique value for each gateway between 1 and maximum allowed.

sonusGatewayName.name: sonusGatewayName
sonusGatewayName.description: The name of the IP Telephony gateway.

sonusGatewayProfName.name: sonusGatewayProfName
sonusGatewayProfName.description: The name of the profile applied to this gateway entry.

sonusGatewayIpAddress.name: sonusGatewayIpAddress
sonusGatewayIpAddress.description: This is signaling Ip address of the gateway.

sonusGatewayPortNum.name: sonusGatewayPortNum
sonusGatewayPortNum.description: This is the port number assigned for the signaling Ip address of the gateway (default is Sonus registered port 2569).

sonusGatewayMaxConn.name: sonusGatewayMaxConn
sonusGatewayMaxConn.description: This is the maximum connections allowed for this gateway to the remote gateway specified by the sonusGatewayName.

sonusGatewayAdminState.name: sonusGatewayAdminState
sonusGatewayAdminState.description: Allow administrator to disable or enable the connection from this gateway to the remote gateway. All connections to the remote gateways are created with its state disabled. Once disabled, the gateway must be enabled to allow calls to proceed again.

sonusGwStatusTable.name: sonusGwStatusTable
sonusGwStatusTable.description: This is a table containing a list of IP telephony gateways in the network.

sonusGwStatusEntry.name: sonusGwStatusEntry
sonusGwStatusEntry.description: Each entry lists the current connections and order of each gateway.

sonusGwStatusIndex.name: sonusGwStatusIndex
sonusGwStatusIndex.description: A unique value for each gateway between 1 and maximum allowed.

sonusGwCurrConnections.name: sonusGwCurrConnections
sonusGwCurrConnections.description: The Current number of connections between this gateway and the remote gateway.

sonusTgMaxCarrierCodes.name: sonusTgMaxCarrierCodes
sonusTgMaxCarrierCodes.description: Maximum number of Carrier Codes for this gateway.

sonusCarrierCodeNextIndex.name: sonusCarrierCodeNextIndex
sonusCarrierCodeNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating a new sonusCarrierCodeEntry

sonusCarrierCodeTable.name: sonusCarrierCodeTable
sonusCarrierCodeTable.description: This is a table containing a list of IP telephony gateways in the network.

sonusCarrierCodeEntry.name: sonusCarrierCodeEntry
sonusCarrierCodeEntry.description: Each entry lists the name and order of each gateway.

sonusCarrierCodeIndex.name: sonusCarrierCodeIndex
sonusCarrierCodeIndex.description: A unique value for each carrier code between 1 and maximum allowed.

sonusCarrierCodeName.name: sonusCarrierCodeName
sonusCarrierCodeName.description: The name assigned to this carrier code.

sonusCarrierCode.name: sonusCarrierCode
sonusCarrierCode.description: This is the carrier code specified by the sonusCarrierCodeName. There are a maximum of up to 4 digits.

sonusCarrierCodeAdminState.name: sonusCarrierCodeAdminState
sonusCarrierCodeAdminState.description: Allow administrator to disable or enable this carrier code. Once disabled, this carrier code must be enabled to allow calls to proceed again.

sonusCarrierCodeNetworkIdType.name: sonusCarrierCodeNetworkIdType
sonusCarrierCodeNetworkIdType.description: The type of network identification for this carrier code

sonusCarrierCodeNetworkIdPlan.name: sonusCarrierCodeNetworkIdPlan
sonusCarrierCodeNetworkIdPlan.description: The network identification plan for this carrier code

sonusTrunkOutOfServiceReason.name: sonusTrunkOutOfServiceReason
sonusTrunkOutOfServiceReason.description: The reason why the Trunk Group is out of service.

sonusTrunkEnabledNotification.name: sonusTrunkEnabledNotification
sonusTrunkEnabledNotification.description: This trap indicates a Trunk Group is now enabled.

sonusTrunkDisabledNotification.name: sonusTrunkDisabledNotification
sonusTrunkDisabledNotification.description: This trap indicates a Trunk Group is now disabled.

sonusTrunkInServiceNotification.name: sonusTrunkInServiceNotification
sonusTrunkInServiceNotification.description: This trap indicates a Trunk Group is now in service.

sonusTrunkOutOfServiceNotification.name: sonusTrunkOutOfServiceNotification
sonusTrunkOutOfServiceNotification.description: This trap indicates that a Trunk Group is out of service.

sonusTrunkDeletedNotification.name: sonusTrunkDeletedNotification
sonusTrunkDeletedNotification.description: This trap indicates a Trunk Group is now deleted.
